telemetry.main

This table represents a stable view of the main ping. It is updated daily.

Schema: mozilla-pipeline-schemas

Scheduling: Airflow

  • additional_properties A JSON string containing any payload properties not present in the schema
  • application
    • architecture
    • build_id
    • channel
    • display_version
    • name
    • platform_version
    • vendor
    • version
    • xpcom_abi
  • client_id
  • creation_date
  • document_id The document ID specified in the URI when the client sent this message
  • environment
    • addons
      • active_addons
        • key
        • value
          • app_disabled True if this add-on cannot be used in the application based on version compatibility, dependencies, and blocklisting. This field is only available after the 'sessionstore-windows-restored' topic is notified.
          • blocklisted Whether or not the add-on appears in the blocklist. This field is only available after the 'sessionstore-windows-restored' topic is notified.
          • description
          • foreign_install
          • has_binary_components True or false depending on whether the add-on has binary components. This is always false since Firefox 60. This field is only available after the 'sessionstore-windows-restored' topic is notified.
          • install_day The days since epoch that the add-on was first installed. This field is only available after the 'sessionstore-windows-restored' topic is notified.
          • is_system Whether or not the add-on is a system add-on. This field is available at startup.
          • is_web_extension Whether or not the add-on is a WebExtension add-on. This field is available at startup.
          • multiprocess_compatible Whether or not the add-on is a compatible with e10s. Since Firefox 61, this is always true. This field is available at startup.
          • name The add-on name, limited to 100 characters. This field is only available after the 'sessionstore-windows-restored' topic is notified.
          • scope Indicates what scope the add-on is installed in, per profile, user, system, or application. This field is available at startup.
          • signed_state The state of the signature of the add-on. This field is only available after the 'sessionstore-windows-restored' topic is notified.
          • type
          • update_day The day the add-on was last updated. This field is optional, but available at startup if present.
          • user_disabled
          • version
      • active_experiment
        • branch
        • id
      • active_gm_plugins
        • key
        • value
          • apply_background_updates Cast into an integer via mozilla-schema-generator. See bug 1611027.
          • user_disabled
          • version
      • active_plugins
        • blocklisted
        • clicktoplay
        • description
        • disabled
        • mime_types
        • name
        • update_day
        • version
      • persona The id of the active persona (theme).
      • theme
        • app_disabled True if this theme cannot be used in the application based on version compatibility, dependencies, and blocklisting.
        • blocklisted Whether or not the theme appears in the blocklist.
        • description
        • foreign_install
        • has_binary_components True or false depending on whether the theme has binary components. This is always false since Firefox 60.
        • id The id of the theme.
        • install_day The days since epoch that the theme was first installed.
        • name The theme name, limited to 100 characters.
        • scope Indicates what scope the theme is installed in, per profile, user, system, or application.
        • update_day The day the theme was last updated.
        • user_disabled Whether or not the user disabled the theme.
        • version The version of the theme.
    • build
      • application_id The application UUID.
      • application_name The application name.
      • architecture The build architecture for the active build.
      • architectures_in_binary For Mac universal builds, this is a string containing a list of architectures delimited by '-'. Architecture sets are always in the same order: ppc > i386 > ppc64 > x86_64 > (future additions). This is only available on Mac.
      • build_id The build ID/date of the application.
      • display_version The display version of the application.
      • hotfix_version
      • platform_version The version of the XULRunner platform.
      • updater_available True if the application was built with the support for the updater component.
      • vendor The application vendor.
      • version The version of the application.
      • xpcom_abi A string tag identifying the binary ABI of the current processor and compiler vtable. This is taken from the TARGET_XPCOM_ABI configure variable. It may not be available on all platforms, especially unusual processor or compiler combinations. The result takes the form -, for example: x86-msvc, ppc-gcc3, ... . This value should almost always be used in combination with the 'OS'.
    • experiments
      • key
      • value
        • branch
        • enrollment_id
        • type
    • partner
      • distribution_id The value of the `distribution.id` pref that identifies the Firefox distribution.
      • distribution_version The value of the `distribution.version` pref.
      • distributor The value of the `app.distributor` pref.
      • distributor_channel The value of the `app.distributor.channel` pref.
      • partner_id The value of the `mozilla.partner.id` pref.
      • partner_names
    • profile
      • creation_date The creation date of the user profile as the integer number of days since UNIX epoch.
      • first_use_date
      • is_stub_profile
      • reset_date The date the user profile was reset, as the integer number of days since UNIX epoch. This is optional.
    • services
      • account_enabled
      • sync_enabled
    • settings
      • addon_compatibility_check_enabled Whether application compatibility is respected for add-ons.
      • attribution
        • campaign Identifier of the particular campaign that led to the download of the product.
        • content Identifier to indicate the particular link within a campaign.
        • experiment funnel experiment parameters, see bug 1567339
        • medium Category of the source, such as 'organic' for a search engine.
        • source Referring partner domain, when install happens via a known partner.
        • ua derived user agent, see bug 1595063
        • variation funnel experiment parameters, see bug 1567339
      • blocklist_enabled True if the blocklist is enabled.
      • default_private_search_engine
      • default_private_search_engine_data
        • load_path
        • name
        • origin
        • submission_url
      • default_search_engine Contains the string identifier or name of the default search engine provider. Deprecated.
      • default_search_engine_data
        • load_path The anonymized path of the engine xml file, e.g. e.g. jar:[app]/omni.ja!browser/engine.xml (where ‘browser’ is the name of the chrome package, not a folder) [profile]/searchplugins/engine.xml [distribution]/searchplugins/common/engine.xml [other]/engine.xml [other]/addEngineWithDetails [other]/addEngineWithDetails:extensionID [http/https]example.com/engine-name.xml [http/https]example.com/engine-name.xml:extensionID
        • name The name of the default search engine.
        • origin The origin of the search engine: the value will be default for engines that are built-in or from distribution partners, verified for user-installed engines with valid verification hashes, unverified for non-default engines without verification hash, and invalid for engines with broken verification hashes.
        • submission_url The HTTP url we would use to search. For privacy, we don’t record this for user-installed engines.
      • e10s_cohort
      • e10s_enabled True if the E10S is enabled.
      • e10s_multi_processes maximum number of processes that will be launched for regular web content
      • intl
        • accept_languages
        • app_locales
        • available_locales
        • regional_prefs_locales
        • requested_locales
        • system_locales
      • is_default_browser Identifier to indicate the particular link within a campaign.
      • is_in_optout_sample
      • launcher_process_state
      • locale The best locale that the application should be localized to.
      • sandbox
        • effective_content_process_level The effective sandbox. The values are OS dependent.
      • search_cohort
      • telemetry_enabled The state of the `toolkit.telemetry.enabled` pref.
      • update
        • auto_download The state of the `app.update.auto` pref.
        • channel The update channel from the defaults only. Does not include the partner bits.
        • enabled The state of the `app.update.enabled` pref.
      • user_prefs
        • key
        • value
    • system
      • apple_model_id The model IDs for Apple desktop devices. This is Mac only.
      • cpu
        • cores The number of physical CPU cores. Desktop only, e.g. 4, or `null` on failure.
        • count The number of logical CPUs. Desktop only, e.g. 8, or `null` on failure.
        • extensions
        • family The CPU family, `null` on failure. Desktop only.
        • l2cache_kb The CPU L2 cache size in KB. `null` on failure. Desktop only.
        • l3cache_kb The CPU L3 cache size in KB. `null` on failure. Desktop only.
        • model The CPU model, `null` on failure. Desktop only.
        • speed_m_hz Only available on Firefox desktop. The CPU clock speed in MHz.
        • stepping The CPU stepping, `null` on failure. Desktop only.
        • vendor The CPU vendor, e.g. 'GenuineIntel', or `null` on failure. Desktop only.
      • device
        • hardware
        • is_tablet
        • manufacturer
        • model
      • gfx
        • adapters
          • description
          • device_id
          • driver
          • driver_date
          • driver_vendor
          • driver_version
          • gpu_active
          • ram
          • subsys_id
          • vendor_id
        • content_backend The name of the content backend.
        • d2d_enabled Whether or not Direct2D is enabled. This is Windows only.
        • d_write_enabled Whether or not DirectWrite is enabled. This is Windows only.
        • features
          • advanced_layers
            • no_constant_buffer_offsetting
            • status
          • compositor The name of the compositor. This is one of 'd3d9', 'd3d11', 'opengl', 'basic', or 'none' ('none' indicates no compositors have been created).
          • d2d
            • status
            • version
          • d3d11
            • blacklisted
            • status
            • texture_sharing
            • version
            • warp
          • gpu_process
            • status
          • webrender
            • status
          • wr_qualified
            • status
        • headless
        • low_end_machine
        • monitors
          • pseudo_display
          • refresh_rate
          • scale
          • screen_height
          • screen_width
      • hdd
        • binary
          • model The model of the hdd where the application binaries are located. This is Windows only.
          • revision The revision of the hdd where the application binaries are located. This is Windows only.
          • type
        • profile
          • model The model of the hdd where the profile directory is located. This is Windows only.
          • revision The revision of the hdd where the profile directory is located. This is Windows only.
          • type
        • system
          • model The model of the hdd where the system files are located. This is Windows only.
          • revision The revision of the hdd where the system files are located. This is Windows only.
          • type
      • is_wow64 The availability of the WoW64 subsystem. This is Windows only.
      • is_wow_arm64
      • memory_mb The machines amount of RAM.
      • os
        • has_prefetch
        • has_superfetch
        • install_year The year Windows was installed. This is Windows only. `null` on failure.
        • kernel_version The kernel version of Android. This is Android only. `null` on failure.
        • locale The locale of the OS, e.g. 'en'. This is `null` on failure.
        • name The name of the OS, e.g. 'Windows_NT'. This is `null` on failure.
        • service_pack_major The Windows service pack major version. This is Windows only. `null` on failure.
        • service_pack_minor The Windows service pack minor version. This is Windows only. `null` on failure.
        • version
        • windows_build_number The Windows build number. This is Windows only. `null` on failure.
        • windows_ubr The Windows UBR. This is Windows 10 only. `null` on failure.
      • sec
        • antispyware The name of the registered antispyware software. Windows only.
        • antivirus The name of the registered antivirus software. Windows only.
        • firewall The name of the registered firewall software. Windows only.
      • virtual_max_mb Total virtual memory size in MB. This is Windows only. `null` on failure.
  • id
  • metadata
    • geo Results of a geographic lookup based on the client's IP address
      • city
      • country An ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code
      • db_version The specific geo database version used for this lookup
      • subdivision1 First major country subdivision, typically a state, province, or county
      • subdivision2 Second major country subdivision; not applicable for most countries
    • header Headers included in the client's HTTP request
      • date Date HTTP header
      • dnt DNT (Do Not Track) HTTP header
      • x_debug_id X-Debug-Id HTTP header
      • x_pingsender_version X-PingSender-Version HTTP header
    • isp Results of ISP lookup based on the client's IP address
      • db_version The specific geo ISP database version used for this lookup
      • name The name of the ISP associated with the client's IP address
      • organization The name of a specific business entity associated with the client's IP address when available; otherwise the ISP name
    • uri Components of the URI to which this ping was sent
      • app_build_id
      • app_name
      • app_update_channel
      • app_version
    • user_agent Parsed components of the client's user agent string
      • browser
      • os
      • version
  • normalized_app_name Set to "Other" if this message contained an unrecognized app name
  • normalized_channel Set to "Other" if this message contained an unrecognized channel name
  • normalized_country_code An ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code
  • normalized_os Set to "Other" if this message contained an unrecognized OS name
  • normalized_os_version
  • payload
    • histograms
      • a11y_consumers A list of known accessibility clients that inject into Firefox process space (see https://dxr.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/source/accessible/windows/msaa/Compatibility.h).
      • a11y_iatable_usage_flag Flag indicating the IAccessibleTable accessibility interface has been used.
      • a11y_instantiated_flag Flag indicating accessibility support has been instantiated.
      • a11y_isimpledom_usage_flag Flag indicating the ISimpleDOM* accessibility interfaces has been used.
      • a11y_tree_update_timing_ms The amount of time taken to update the accessibility tree (ms)
      • a11y_uia_detection_timing_ms The amount of time the parent process blocked while detecting a UIA client.
      • about_config_features_usage Record number of times particular features on about:config are used
      • addon_manager_upgrade_ui_shown Recorded when the addon manager shows the modal upgrade UI. Should only be recorded once per upgrade.
      • alerts_service_dnd_enabled XUL-only: whether the user has toggled do not disturb.
      • alerts_service_dnd_supported_flag Whether the do not disturb option is supported. True if the browser uses XUL alerts.
      • application_reputation_allowlist_match For each Application Reputation lookup against both the V2 and V4 Google lists, note which version of the allow list returned a match (0 = no match, 1 = match only V2, 2 = match only V4, 3 = match both V2 and V4)
      • application_reputation_binary Whether or not the file examined by download protection is a binary type (or it's not possible to tell because the filename is missing).
      • application_reputation_binary_archive Whether a binary file examined by download protection is one of the common archive formats.
      • application_reputation_binary_type Whether or not the file examined by download protection is a binary type (or it's not possible to tell because the filename is missing).
      • application_reputation_blocklist_match For each Application Reputation lookup against both the V2 and V4 Google lists, note which version of block list returned a match (0 = no match, 1 = match only V2, 2 = match only V4, 3 = match both V2 and V4)
      • application_reputation_count Application reputation query count (both local and remote)
      • application_reputation_hash_length Whether the hash included in application reputation lookups is valid or broken in some way.
      • application_reputation_local Application reputation local results (0=ALLOW, 1=BLOCK, 2=NONE)
      • application_reputation_reason The reason application reputation service blocks or allows the download.
      • application_reputation_remote_lookup_response_time Server response time to remote lookup request (ms).
      • application_reputation_remote_lookup_timeout Recorded when application reputation remote lookup is performed, `true` is recorded if the lookup times out.
      • application_reputation_server Status of the application reputation remote lookup (0=OK, 1=failed, 2=invalid protobuf response)
      • application_reputation_server_2 Network status of the application reputation remote lookup
      • application_reputation_server_verdict Application reputation remote verdict (0=SAFE, 1=DANGEROUS, 2=UNCOMMON, 3=POTENTIALLY_UNWANTED, 4=DANGEROUS_HOST, 5=UNKNOWN)
      • application_reputation_should_block Overall (local or remote) application reputation verdict (shouldBlock=false is OK).
      • apz_aware_key_listeners The percentage of pages with a non-passive key event on the path to the root scrolling element that would disable APZ key scrolling. This is tracked for non system principal windows, so it applies to toplevel windows and subframes/iframes, but not chrome windows.
      • apz_aware_mousemove_listeners The percentage of pages with a mousemove listener anywhere in the document that would disable APZ key scrolling. This is tracked for non system principal windows, so it applies to toplevel windows and subframes/iframes, but not chrome windows.
      • async_animation_content_too_large_frame_size The number of pixels of the frame for each time we encountered a layer that was so large we decided not to run its animations on the compositor.
      • async_animation_content_too_large_percentage The ratio of the frame size (in total number of pixels) to the relative limit (~viewport size plus some tolerance factor, typically 12.5% in each dimension, i.e. ~27% tolerance in total area) for each time we encountered a layer that was so large we decided not to run its animations on the compositor expressed as a percentage (e.g. 130 = frame area was 30% larger than the relative limit)
      • async_animation_frame_size The number of pixels of the frame each time we potentially run a transform animation on the compositor. Intended for comparison with ASYNC_ANIMATION_CONTENT_TOO_LARGE_FRAME_SIZE.
      • audio_mft_output_null_samples How many times the audio MFT decoder returns success but output nothing.
      • audio_track_silence_proportion In order to know how many silent audio track in the web comparing to other normal media, we record the silence proportion of audio track of media element. The range of value is from 0% - 100%.
      • audiostream_backend_used The operating system audio back-end used when successfully opening an audio stream, or whether the failure occurred on the first try or not
      • audiostream_first_open_ms The length of time (in milliseconds) for the first open of AudioStream.
      • audiostream_later_open_ms The length of time (in milliseconds) for the subsequent opens of AudioStream.
      • aushelper_cpu_error_code The error code from the aushelper system add-on when querying the registry for CPU information for bug 1296630 (see browser/extensions/aushelper/bootstrap.js).
      • aushelper_cpu_result_code Whether the system is affected by bug 1296630 (1=No, 2=Yes, 3=Error, and 4=Unknown).
      • aushelper_websense_error_code The error code from the aushelper system add-on when gathering information on Websense (see browser/extensions/aushelper/bootstrap.js).
      • aushelper_websense_reg_exists Whether the system has a Websense InstallVersion registry value (see browser/extensions/aushelper/bootstrap.js).
      • auto_rejected_translation_offers A number of auto-rejected tranlation offers
      • autoplay_default_setting_change counts the number of times a user changed the default autoplay behavior to each setting during a subsession.
      • autoplay_sites_setting_change The number of times the user adds a site to the allow list, removes a site from the allow list, adds a site to the block list and removes a site from the block list.
      • backgroundfilesaver_thread_count Maximum number of concurrent threads reached during a given download session
      • bad_fallback_font system fallback font can't be used
      • base_font_families_per_page Number of font-family names used that resolved to base system fonts
      • bfcache_combo The common combinations of BFCacheStatus when we determine whether the page can be BFCached or not; If it's BFCached, we record BFCache_Success; Success_Not_Toplevel represents the number of not the only top level document in BrowsingContextGroup's documents that are BFCached, and BFCache_Success includes Success_Not_Toplevel; If it's not and it falls under common failure reasons combinations, we record the corresponding combination; Otherwise, we record Other to indicate this is not a common failure
      • bfcache_page_restored Whether bfcache is used when loading a page from session history
      • blink_filesystem_used Webkit/Blink filesystem used
      • blocklist_sync_file_load Whether blocklist.xml was loaded synchronously. True means it was loaded synchronously, false means it was preloaded asynchronously.
      • box_align_props_in_blocks_flag Whether we have layed out any display:block containers with not-yet-supported properties from CSS Box Align.
      • br_9_2_1_subject_alt_names Baseline Requirements section 9.2.1: subject alternative names extension (0: ok, 1 or more: error)
      • br_9_2_2_subject_common_name Baseline Requirements section 9.2.2: subject common name field (0: present, in subject alt. names; 1: not present; 2: not present in subject alt. names)
      • browser_attribution_errors Count for the number of errors encountered trying to read the attribution data from the stub installer.
      • browser_is_assist_default The result of the default browser check for assist intent.
      • browser_is_user_default The result of the startup default desktop browser check.
      • browser_is_user_default_error True if the browser was unable to determine if the browser was set as default.
      • browser_set_default_always_check True if the profile has `browser.shell.checkDefaultBrowser` set to true.
      • browser_set_default_dialog_prompt_rawcount The number of times that a profile has seen the 'Set Default Browser' dialog.
      • browser_set_default_error True if the browser was unable to set Firefox as the default browser
      • browser_set_default_result Result of the Set Default Browser dialog (0=Use Firefox + 'Always perform check' unchecked, 1=Use Firefox + 'Always perform check' checked, 2=Not Now + 'Always perform check' unchecked, 3=Not Now + 'Always perform check' checked)
      • browser_shim_usage_blocked Counts the number of times a CPOW shim was blocked from being created by browser code.
      • browserprovider_xul_import_bookmarks Number of bookmarks in the original XUL places database
      • bucket_order_errors Number of histograms with bucket order errors
      • busy_tab_abandoned Records a value each time a tab that is showing the loading throbber is interrupted. Desktop only.
      • cache_device_search_2 Time to search cache (ms)
      • cache_disk_search_2 Time to search disk cache (ms)
      • cache_lm_inconsistent Cache discovered inconsistent last-modified entry
      • cache_memory_search_2 Time to search memory cache (ms)
      • cache_offline_search_2 Time to search offline cache (ms)
      • cache_service_lock_wait_2 Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms)
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_2 Time spent waiting on the cache service lock on the main thread (ms)
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nsasyncdoomevent_run Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSASYNCDOOMEVENT_RUN
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nsblockoncachethreadevent_run Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSBLOCKONCACHETHREADEVENT_RUN
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_close Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_CLOSE
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_doom Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_DOOM
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_doomandfailpendingrequests Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_DOOMANDFAILPENDINGREQUESTS
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_getcacheelement Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_GETCACHEELEMENT
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_getclientid Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_GETCLIENTID
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_getdatasize Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_GETDATASIZE
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_getdeviceid Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_GETDEVICEID
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_getexpirationtime Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_GETEXPIRATIONTIME
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_getfetchcount Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_GETFETCHCOUNT
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_getfile Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_GETFILE
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_getkey Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_GETKEY
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_getlastfetched Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_GETLASTFETCHED
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_getlastmodified Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_GETLASTMODIFIED
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_getmetadataelement Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_GETMETADATAELEMENT
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_getpredicteddatasize Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_GETPREDICTEDDATASIZE
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_getsecurityinfo Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_GETSECURITYINFO
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_getstoragedatasize Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_GETSTORAGEDATASIZE
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_getstoragepolicy Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_GETSTORAGEPOLICY
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_isstreambased Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_ISSTREAMBASED
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_markvalid Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_MARKVALID
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_openinputstream Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_OPENINPUTSTREAM
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_openoutputstream Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_OPENOUTPUTSTREAM
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_requestdatasizechange Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_REQUESTDATASIZECHANGE
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_setcacheelement Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_SETCACHEELEMENT
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_setdatasize Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_SETDATASIZE
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_setexpirationtime Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_SETEXPIRATIONTIME
      • cache_service_lock_wait_mainthread_nscacheentrydescriptor_setmetadataelement Time spent waiting on the cache service lock (ms) on the main thread in NSCACHEENTRYDESCRIPTOR_SETMETADATAELEMENT

      • fx_tab_switch_spinner_visible_long_ms Firefox: If the spinner interstitial displays during tab switching, records the time in ms the graphic is visible. This probe is similar to FX_TAB_SWITCH_SPINNER_VISIBLE_MS, but is for truly degenerate cases.

      • fx_urlbar_selected_result_method The input method the user used to select a result in the urlbar. 'enter' => The user hit the Enter key on the heuristic result at index 0. 'enterSelection' => The user chose a non-heuristic result (in exotic ways) and then hit the Enter key. 'click' => The user clicked a result with the mouse. 'arrowEnterSelection' => The user chose a non-heuristic result using arrow keys and then hit the Enter key. 'tabEnterSelection' => The user chose a non-heuristic result using tab at least once and then hit the Enter key. 'rightClickEnter' => The user chose a non-heuristic result using right click and then hit the Enter key.

      • urlclassifier_cl_check_time Time spent per classifier lookup (ms)
      • urlclassifier_classifylocal_time Time spent inside ClassifyLocalWithTables (ms)
      • urlclassifier_completion_error SafeBrowsing v4 hash completion error (0 = success, 1 = parsing failure, 2 = unknown threat type)
      • urlclassifier_lc_completions Size of the completion cache in entries
      • urlclassifier_lc_prefixes Size of the prefix cache in entries
      • urlclassifier_lookup_time_2 Time spent per dbservice lookup (ms)
      • urlclassifier_match_result The result of each URL lookup against both google and google4 lists. (0 = no match, 1 = V2 prefix only, 2 = V4 prefix only, 3 = V2 and V4 prefixes, 4 = V2 and V4 completions, 5 = V2 completion only, 6 = V4 completion only, 7 = V2 completion and v4 prefix, 8 = V2 prefix and V4 completion, 9 = unexpected result)
      • urlclassifier_match_threat_type_result Whether or not a full URL match is of the same threat type on V2 and V4. (0 = same, otherwise the value is a bit flag where 0x01 = V2 phishing, 0x02 = V2 malware, 0x04 = V2 unwanted, 0x08 = V4 phishing, 0x10 = V4 malware, 0x20 = V4 unwanted)
      • urlclassifier_negative_cache_duration Negative cache duration (ms) received in fullhash response from any v4 provider
      • urlclassifier_positive_cache_duration Positive cache duration (ms) received in fullhash response from any v4 provider
      • urlclassifier_ps_construct_time Time spent constructing PrefixSet from DB (ms)
      • urlclassifier_ps_fallocate_time Time spent fallocating PrefixSet (ms)
      • urlclassifier_ps_fileload_time Time spent loading PrefixSet from file (ms)
      • urlclassifier_shutdown_time Time spent per dbservice shutdown (ms)
      • urlclassifier_threathit_network_error Whether or not an error was encountered while sending a Safe Browsing ThreatHit report. (0=sucess, 1=unknown error, 2=already connected, 3=not connected, 4=connection refused,5=net timeout, 6=offline, 7=port access not allowed, 8=net reset, 9=net interrupt, 10=proxy connection refused, 11=partial transfer, 12=inadequate security, 13=unknown host, 14=dns lookup queue full, 15=unknown proxy host)
      • urlclassifier_threathit_remote_status Server HTTP status code from Safe Browsing ThreatHit report. (0=1xx, 1=200, 2=2xx, 3=204, 4=3xx, 5=400, 6=4xx, 7=403, 8=404, 9=408, 10=413, 11=5xx, 12=502|504|511, 13=503, 14=505, 15=Other)
      • urlclassifier_ui_events URL CLassifier-related (aka Safe Browsing) UI events. See nsIUrlClassifierUITelemetry.idl for the specific values.

      • urlclassifier_vlps_fallocate_time Time spent fallocating Variable-Length PrefixSet (ms)
      • urlclassifier_vlps_fileload_time Time spent loading Variable-Length PrefixSet from file (ms)
      • urlclassifier_vlps_load_corrupt Whether or not a variable-length prefix set loaded from disk is corrupted (true = file corrupted).
      • urlclassifier_vlps_long_prefixes Length of the first 20 long prefixes (> 4 bytes) received in a Safe Browsing V4 table during an update.
      • urlclassifier_vlps_metadata_corrupt Whether or not the metadata for a variable-length prefix set loaded from disk is corrupted (true = file corrupted).
